Deprecated Methods
com.j256.ormlite.stmt.Where.clear()
          Should now use Where.reset(). 
com.j256.ormlite.stmt.UpdateBuilder.clear()
          Renamed to be UpdateBuilder.reset(). 
com.j256.ormlite.stmt.StatementBuilder.clear()
          Renamed to be StatementBuilder.reset(). 
com.j256.ormlite.stmt.QueryBuilder.clear()
          Renamed to be QueryBuilder.reset(). 
com.j256.ormlite.stmt.DeleteBuilder.clear()
          Renamed to be DeleteBuilder.reset(). 
com.j256.ormlite.dao.RuntimeExceptionDao.isAutoCommit()
           
com.j256.ormlite.dao.Dao.isAutoCommit()
          You should use the Dao.isAutoCommit(DatabaseConnection) method instead. 
com.j256.ormlite.stmt.QueryBuilder.limit(int)
          Should use QueryBuilder.limit(Long) 
com.j256.ormlite.stmt.QueryBuilder.offset(int)
          Should use QueryBuilder.offset(Long) 
com.j256.ormlite.dao.RuntimeExceptionDao.setAutoCommit(boolean)
           
com.j256.ormlite.dao.Dao.setAutoCommit(boolean)
          You should use the Dao.setAutoCommit(DatabaseConnection, boolean) method instead. 
com.j256.ormlite.field.DatabaseFieldConfig.setForeignCollectionForeignColumnName(String)
          You should use DatabaseFieldConfig.setForeignCollectionForeignFieldName(String) 
com.j256.ormlite.field.DatabaseFieldConfig.setForeignCollectionMaxEagerForeignCollectionLevel(int)
          Should use DatabaseFieldConfig.setForeignCollectionMaxEagerLevel(int) 
com.j256.ormlite.field.DatabaseFieldConfig.setForeignCollectionOrderColumn(String)
          You should use DatabaseFieldConfig.setForeignCollectionOrderColumnName(String) 
com.j256.ormlite.field.DatabaseFieldConfig.setMaxEagerForeignCollectionLevel(int)
          Should use DatabaseFieldConfig.setForeignCollectionMaxEagerLevel(int) 
 

Deprecated Annotation Type Elements
com.j256.ormlite.field.ForeignCollectionField.foreignColumnName
          This has been renamed as ForeignCollectionField.foreignFieldName() to make it more consistent to how it works. 
com.j256.ormlite.field.ForeignCollectionField.maxEagerForeignCollectionLevel
          Should use ForeignCollectionField.maxEagerLevel()
